{
  "texts": [
    "The memory overhead of the tree data structure used to group the microlenses into cells may grow too large with the number of microlenses for a single processor to handle.",
    "For this reason, a parallel version has been developed (Garsden and Lewis 2010) that overcomes this by distributing the computations across many nodes on a computer cluster.",
    "Using this approach, magnification patterns of up to a billion microlenses can be computed in realistic timescales.",
    "Another approach to speed up the solution of Eq.",
    "(33) is to reduce the number of rays shot, N rays, as does the inverse polygon mapping technique developed by Mediavilla et al. (2006 Mediavilla et al. (, 2011)), Shalyapin et al. (2021)."
  ]
}